issue.title: Helm chart value, tolerations, is not applied to webhook deployment
issue.body: Operator 4.1.3 includes Helm chart values for both `nodeSelector` and `tolerations`; however, only the `nodeSelector` value is correctly applied to both the operator and webhook deployments. The `tolerations` value needs to also apply to the webhook's deployment.

release.name: Operator 4.1.4
release.body:
<!-- Release notes generated using configuration in .github/release.yml at v4.1.4 -->

#### Other Changes
- The default WebLogic Monitoring Exporter version is now 2.1.8.
- Container image now uses Oracle Java SE 21 LTS

#### Bug Fixes
- Recreated container images following the [October 2023 Oracle Linux Bulletin](https://www.oracle.com/security-alerts/linuxbulletinoct2023.html)
- Resolved [issue 4426](https://github.com/oracle/weblogic-kubernetes-operator/issues/4426) by adding tolerations to webhook deployment

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/oracle/weblogic-kubernetes-operator/compare/v4.1.3...v4.1.4
